cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.CC, cs.DC, cs.AL

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the construction of compressed suffix arrays and trees, which are important data structures for text indexing and search.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as compressed indexes are commonly used in information retrieval systems to efficiently store and search large collections of documents.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper discusses the time and space complexity of the algorithms.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions parallelization as a possible future direction for improving the algorithms.
- cs.AL (Algorithms) is also possible as the paper presents new algorithms for constructing compressed indexes.
